prompt:
Add two local models to the declarative Ollama config and set a safe default context length on host classic-laddie.

## Context
`hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix` configures Ollama declaratively. The current block (~line 218) is:

    services.ollama = {
      enable = true;
      package = pkgs.ollama-cuda;
      loadModels = [ "gemma4:26b" ];
    };

This host has an RTX 4090 (24GB VRAM). We want two more models managed declaratively, plus a context-length cap. The cap matters because when Ollama auto-selects a 32K context for a ~20GB 32B model, the KV cache overflows 24GB VRAM and spills ~23% of the model onto the CPU, which tanks throughput (and previously contributed to an out-of-RAM hard lock). Capping the default context keeps the 32B dense models fully GPU-resident.

## Change (only this block, in hosts/classic-laddie/default.nix)
Update the services.ollama block to:

    services.ollama = {
      enable = true;
      package = pkgs.ollama-cuda;
      loadModels = [
        "gemma4:26b"
        "qwen3:32b"
        "qwen2.5-coder:32b"
      ];
      environmentVariables = {
        # Cap the default context so the 32B dense models (qwen3, qwen2.5-coder)
        # stay fully resident in the 4090's 24GB VRAM. At Ollama's auto-selected
        # 32K context the KV cache overflowed VRAM and spilled ~23% of the model
        # to the CPU, badly hurting throughput. 8192 is a safe default for every
        # model here; override per request with options.num_ctx when more is needed.
        OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH = "8192";
      };
    };

Do not change anything else (open-webui, package, etc.).

## Verify the option name
`services.ollama.environmentVariables` is the correct NixOS option (attrset of string env vars). Confirm it evaluates — if for some reason this nixpkgs revision names it differently, find the correct option via `nixos-option` or the nixpkgs ollama module and use that, but prefer environmentVariables.

## Acceptance criteria
- The classic-laddie configuration evaluates and builds. Verify with the project's canonical check (look in .github/workflows or any justfile first); otherwise:
  `nix build --no-link .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel --dry-run`
  Report exactly what you ran and the result.
- Diff is limited to the services.ollama block.

## Constraints
- Follow the repo CLAUDE.md: NO Co-Authored-By lines, and do NOT mention Claude/AI/LLM anywhere in the commit message or PR body.
- PR description: explain that this adds qwen3:32b and qwen2.5-coder:32b to declaratively-managed models and pins OLLAMA_CONTEXT_LENGTH=8192 to keep 32B models from spilling out of the 4090's VRAM.
